  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate", 
    "date": "2018-03-22T04:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Comprehensive Opioid Recovery Centers Act of 2018\n\nThis bill amends the Public Health Service Act to require the Department of Health and Human Services to award grants to establish or operate comprehensive opioid recovery centers. Priority for grants must be given to entities located in states or Indian country with a high per capita drug overdose mortality rate. Each center must carry out specified outreach activities and specified treatment and recovery services."
